<topic template="Default" modified="2020-06-15T16:36:04.342+03:00" lasteditedby="User1" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Reusing</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Reusing</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">After publishing the current version of the component, Cobalt and eWizard users are able to install your component (use the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#c7254e; background-color:#f9f2f4;" translate="true">co install [component-name]</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true"> command), and use it in their own projects like any other component created by the Cobalt Dev team. In order to add a component to the eWizard editor - </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="weblink" href="https://docs.ewizard.io/doc/ewizard-v1-12-0/#8437" styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">Gallery sidebar</link><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">, it has to be added to eWizard via the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">Add to eWizard</text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true"> button of the component record in the Components Gallery:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><image src="Screen-Shot-2018-05-31-at-10.32.08-AM.png" scale="23.73%" width="662" height="137" padding="0 0 1 0" styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-size:12pt;"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">As a result, the component appears in the eWizard&apos;s </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">Gallery sidebar </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">editor:</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><image src="Screen-Shot-2018-05-31-at-10.44.42-AM-1024x542.jpg" scale="64.53%" width="661" height="350" padding="0 0 1 0" styleclass="Image Caption" style="font-size:12pt;"></image></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal" style="line-height:1.25; background-color:#ffffff; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">However, if the version of the Core component used in a custom component is not compatible with the Core version used inside the presentation, your component will not be added to </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#424242;" translate="true">Gallery Sidebar.</text></para>
  </body>
